 from pinn cpqhou se hou compaq com steve pinn x four four three zero four subject re request gyro souvlaki sauce organization compaq computer corp distribution usa x newsreader tin version one one pl eight lines three two michael trofimoff tron fafnir la locus com wrote hi all would anyone out there in net land happen to have an authentic sure fire way of making this great sauce that is used to adorn gyro s and souvlaki thanks i have a receipe at home that was posted to me by one of our fellow netters about a month ago i am recalling this from memory but i think i m fairly close by the way it was great one pint of plain yogurt one two med sized cucumber finely shredded three cloves of garlic more or less by taste one four tsp dill weed the yogurt is dumped into a strainer lined with a coffee filter and allowed to drain at least two hours you can adjust the consistancy of the sauce by increasing this time up to two four hours the shredded cuc is drained the same way mix it all together and let it steep for at least two hours it s better the next day and enjoy steve